    <p>At the beginning of your college career, you no doubt are filled with a bunch of questions and not very many answers. Curiosity about what your life will be like in and out of school, and being even somewhat tangential to the technology sphere means that you have no doubt become aware of Generative AI ‚Äî and I‚Äôd wager have many questions, concerns, and ideas.</p>

    <p>Whether you‚Äôre just stepping into your first computing class or you‚Äôve already dabbled in code, one thing is clear: AI is going to be a part of your journey. A big part.</p>

    <p>This guide is here to help you navigate that. Not as a lecture, and not as a warning ‚Äî but as a toolkit. Whether you‚Äôre curious about what AI can do, cautious about its role in education, or just looking for ways to make your study sessions a little more productive and tailored, this guide is built for you.</p>

    <p><strong>Our goal here is simple:</strong></p>

    <p>I want to show you how to work with AI ‚Äî not for it, and not have it work for you blindly, but using it as a powerful assistant, while still keeping your own skills sharp and your learning front and center. You are still in the driver‚Äôs seat.</p>

